<TEXT>
<P>
Kareem Hooks a Deal: Kareem Abdul Jabbar has slam-dunked a two-year deal with 
Laurel Entertainment to do TV and film projects. 
</P>
<P>
His production company, Kareem Productions, has joined with the subsidiary of 
Spelling Entertainment under a non-exclusive agreement, it was announced 
Wednesday. For the team's first project, Jabbar will be involved in a TV movie 
about the life of Vernon Johns, one of the first black activist ministers in 
the South and a mentor to the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. Ken Fink, who did a 
segment about Johns for "Saturday Night With Connie Chung," will direct the 
project. BETH KLEID 
