<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : MAN KILLED BY ROBBER WHILE WALKING TO WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A South-Central Los Angeles man was robbed and fatally shot Thursday morning as 
he and his wife walked to work, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Donay Serrano, 29, was taken to USC County Medical Center where he 
underwent emergency surgery, police said. He died a few hours later. 
</P>
<P>
The couple was walking south on 42nd Street about 5 a.m. when a man jumped into 
their path and demanded money, Serrano's wife told police. 
</P>
<P>
Serrano gave the gunman one or two dollars, which prompted the robber to shove 
his handgun into Serrano's stomach. 
</P>
<P>
They struggled over the gun and the man shot Serrano in the chest. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman ran to a car, possibly a white Ford Escort, and drove away, police 
said. 
</P>
