<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : COCAINE SUSPECT, 46, FOUND DEAD IN JAIL 
CELL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 46-year-old man in custody on narcotics-related charges was found dead in his 
Parker Center jail cell Thursday and an autopsy was pending to determine how he 
died, police said. 
</P>
<P>
A jailer discovered the man during a routine cell check about 3:30 p.m., Lt. 
William Hall said. Police declined to release the man's identity, pending 
notification of relatives. 
</P>
<P>
There were no obvious signs of trauma to the body, Hall said. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators did not believe the man was involved in any arguments with 
jailers or any of the 14 other prisoners housed in the same cell area, Hall 
said. The man was arrested Wednesday in South-Central Los Angeles for allegedly 
trying to sell cocaine to undercover narcotics agents. 
</P>
