<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN, 92, APPARENTLY KILLS WOMAN, SELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 92-year-old North Hollywood man apparently shot his 42-year-old maid to death 
Thursday and then killed himself, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
The bodies of Shirley Lynn Keever and Ben Walter Schwartz were found at 2:15 
p.m. by officers responding to a report of shots being fired at an apartment 
house in the 6300 block of Whitsett Street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
"They're calling it a murder-suicide," said Sgt. Tom Toutant. 
</P>
<P>
Schwartz apparently shot Keever several times in the upper torso and then shot 
himself once in the head with a .38-caliber semiautomatic pistol, Detective 
David Alfred said. 
</P>
<P>
The bodies were found about 10 feet apart. 
</P>
<P>
Detectives had not determined the cause of the shooting, but neighbors reported 
that the two argued shortly before the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
"It was loud enough to where the neighbors were hearing them yelling at each 
other," Alfred said. 
</P>
<P>
Keever had been living in the apartment with Schwartz for about two months. 
Neighbors reported hearing loud arguments between the two on previous 
occasions, Alfred said. 
</P>
<P>
Neighbors said Schwartz had lived in the apartment for 2 1/2 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
