<HEADLINE>
<P>
'FAIR CONTRACT' URGED FOR POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The continued freedom from the invasions of rampant crime and violence is at 
stake in Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
Few cities in Los Angeles County actually have the sense of security that we in 
Torrance have. 
</P>
<P>
However, these freedoms can be taken away quickly if we do not invest our 
monies and resources in the people who protect this fine city and its liberty. 
</P>
<P>
The men and women of the Torrance police force are directly responsible for the 
high quality of life that we enjoy daily. They are willing to put their lives 
on the line so that Torrance can be the haven that it is day after day. During 
this time the police officers are negotiating with the city for a new pay and 
benefit contract, I ask that the City Council in their wisdom will recognize 
the commitment of these men and women and give them a fair and adequate 
contract. 
</P>
<P>
I want our city to pay the price it takes to ensure the freedoms we still have. 
</P>
<P>
JONATHAN and ROXANNE 
</P>
<P>
TRIMPER 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
