<P>
Auto Contract Proposals Made: The United Auto Workers union considered the 
first comprehensive contract proposals from General Motors Corp. and Ford Motor 
Co., and waited for Chrysler Corp's offer today. 
</P>
<P>
Their contents remain a mystery. GM said only that a proposal for a new 
three-year national contract had been given to the union. Ford and the UAW said 
there would be no statements, and UAW locals around the country said they knew 
nothing about the details of the proposals. 
</P>
