<P>
$52-Million Fine upheld: Russell County Circuit Judge Donald McGlothin Jr. 
ordered the filed a joint motion to dismiss the fines after settling their 
10-month-long strike Feb. 19. 
</P>
<P>
/The walkout involved 1,200 striking miners in Virginia and Kentucky. McGlothin 
agreed to dismiss $11.2 million in fines to compensate Pittston for losses 
caused by union efforts to limit coal production. He upheld the remaining $52 
million owed to the state and to Dickenson and Russell counties in Virginia, 
where most of the strike action took place, union leaders payments by the 
United Mine Workers although both Pittston Coal Group Inc. and the union had 
said they were reviewing McGlothin's ruling. 
</P>
