<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 QUAKES ROCK JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three earthquakes, each with a magnitude of 5, jolted central Japan on Thursday 
morning and disrupted rail traffic for commuters, officials said. No damage or 
injuries were reported. 
</P>
