<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: THOUSAND OAKS; 
</P>
<P>
MAN CONVICTED OF 89 MOLESTATION CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Ventura County Superior Court jury has convicted a Thousand Oaks man of 89 
child molestation charges after he repeatedly abused two young girls over a 
period of six years. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Ceballos, 57, was found guilty after the girls, now 11 and 15, 
testified that he attacked them between 1984 and his arrest in January. 
</P>
<P>
Ceballos denied their accusations. 
</P>
<P>
The molestations were revealed when one girl complained to her teacher, who 
called police and the Ventura County Public Social Services Agency, Deputy 
Dist. Atty. Michael K. Frawley said. 
</P>
<P>
The jury found Ceballos guilty on Wednesday of 23 molestation charges involving 
the younger girl and 66 charges involving the older girl. 
</P>
<P>
His conviction included 13 charges of committing a lewd and lascivious act with 
a child age 14 or 15, each of which carries a maximum penalty of eight years in 
prison. Each of the others carries a maximum penalty of three years in prison. 
Sentencing is scheduled Sept. 21. MACK REED 
</P>
</TEXT>
