<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
HOAXER CLAIMS TO HOLD HUSBANDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two women from Thousand Oaks are the latest targets of a man who calls married 
women, claims he has their husbands bound at gunpoint and sometimes demands 
$5,000 ransom, officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
At least 10 women in Camarillo, Moorpark, Thousand Oaks and Ventura have been 
contacted since July 25, Ventura County Sheriff's Detective Scott Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
None of the women's husbands have been abducted, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The caller appears to select his victims from telephone book listings that 
include both spouses' first names, Miller said. All the calls were made between 
7 and 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
Miller asked that anyone who receives such a call feign cooperation to get 
detailed information before hanging up and immediately contacting the Sheriff's 
Department. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
