<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONTCLAIR PREP, DEREK SPARKS TEAM FOR EARLY POLL POSITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN MURPHY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Montclair Prep, featuring one of the country's top running backs in senior 
Derek Sparks, is ranked No. 1 in the Southern Section Division X preseason 
poll. Montclair Prep is the only Valley-area school to be ranked in a top spot. 
</P>
<P>
The Mounties, stopped one game shy of the Division IX championship game in 
1989, return 18 starters including Donovan Roy (6-foot-6 1/2, 280), wide 
receiver/safety Leland Sparks and wide receiver/cornerback Greg Cole. 
</P>
<P>
Sparks, ranked among the top 25 running backs in America by SuperPrep magazine, 
rushed for 1,944 yards and scored 35 touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
The Southern Section has placed Montclair Prep and the rest of the Alpha League 
in Division X. 
</P>
<P>
Two Golden League teams -- Quartz Hill (No. 5) and Canyon (No. 9) -- are tabbed 
in the top 10 in the league's first year in Division I. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks of the Marmonte League, which returns 14 lettermen, ranks No. 5 
in the Division II poll after an 11-1-1 season in '89. League rival Westlake, 
led by quarterback Todd Preston, is ranked No. 9 and Ventura of the Channel 
League and Channel Islands of the Marmonte League are listed in teams to watch. 
</P>
<P>
Traditional Foothill League power Hart, with 23 returning lettermen and coming 
off a 10-2 season, is ranked No. 7 in the Division III poll and Notre Dame, 
making the jump from Division VII to Division III in the new Mission League, is 
ranked No. 8. 
</P>
<P>
Pass-happy Santa Clara of the Frontier League is ranked No. 8 in Division VIII, 
while league rivals Santa Paula and Fillmore are tabbed as teams to watch. 
BRIAN MURPHY 
</P>
</TEXT>
