<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bowl Protest: The American Federation of Musicians Local 47 is protesting -- 
with a program insert -- the engagement of the Seattle Symphony, a non-union 
orchestra, at Hollywood Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
According to Bernie Fleischer, AFM Local 47 president, program inserts in 
10,000 Bowl programs this weekend will notify concertgoers. Led by music 
director Gerard Schwarz, the Seattle orchestra plays tonight and Saturday. A 
spokesman for the L.A. Philharmonic Assn. said Thursday of the insert: "We are 
complying with a request from the Musicians Union, which represents our 
Philharmonic players." BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
