<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eric Dickerson was a no-show at the Indianapolis Colts' training camp in 
Anderson, Ind., once again refusing to report for a scheduled re-examination of 
his injured hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson has spent the last two weeks at a Houston clinic where he has been 
undergoing rehabilitation for the non-football injury after failing a team 
physical Aug. 6. 
</P>
<P>
He was asked to return to Indianapolis so that team physicians could evaluate 
his progress. 
</P>
<P>
Dickerson, who was bothered by a hamstring injury in his right leg last season, 
suffered the injury to his left leg while working on his own during the 
off-season. The team therefore considers the injury unrelated to football and 
cannot order Dickerson to report for the physical since he is not being paid by 
the club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
