<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The biggest battle in Williamsport, Pa., at the Little League World Series 
pitted a dozen groundskeepers against the rain and mud. 
</P>
<P>
The dirty dozen slogged through the mud, rebuilding part of the Lamade Stadium 
infield, covering and then uncovering the infield with a tarp three times. But 
they couldn't beat the elements, forcing postponement of the East-South 
quarterfinal game. 
</P>
<P>
That means the championship game of the World Series won't be played as 
scheduled on Saturday and has been moved to Sunday. 
</P>
