<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United States, led by Terry Lewis' strong fencing performance, took the 
lead in the team competition at the women's World Modern Pentathlon 
Championships in Linkoping, Sweden. 
</P>
<P>
Eva Fjellerup of Denmark won 35 of 45 matches for 1,072 points to lead the 
individual competition. Lewis had a 30-15 won-lost record and was tied for 
fourth with 952 points. 
</P>
<P>
The United States had an overall score of 2,688 points and led West Germany by 
24 points going into today's swimming and pistol shooting. 
</P>
