<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOJAROWICZ FORUM IN SANTA MONICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Monica Museum of Art and the Coalition for Freedom of Expression have 
scheduled a series of eight discussions about the museum's current "Tongues of 
Flame" exhibition by controversial New York-based artist David Wojarowicz. 
</P>
<P>
Artists -- including Jacki Apple, Renee Petropoulos, Diane Buckler, Ed Landler, 
John O'Brein and Margaret Lazzari -- will talk about Wojarowicz's work and 
address issues of censorship that have been raised by the show. 
</P>
<P>
The free discussions will begin at 1 and 3 p.m. this Saturday and Sunday and 
Sept. 1 and 2 at the museum, 2437 Main St., Santa Monica. Information: (213) 
399-0433 or (213) 851-0737. 
</P>
