<TEXT>
<P>
FOR SALE? Every day the federal government's Resolution Trust Corp. hangs onto 
Irvine-based Lincoln S&amp;L, it loses money. 
</P>
<P>
In the first 3 months of this year, it lost $133 million. Now that a federal 
court has cleared the way for government to dispose of Lincoln (D1), what is 
the likelihood of finding a buyer to take over the thrift? "About nil," says 
Brea-based S&amp;L analyst Gerry Findley. "There is more prospect of them 
dismantling it and selling off pieces." The feds won't speculate. Mark I. 
